FAQs 
1. What are the language requirements for studying in Cyprus?
Most programs in Cyprus are taught in English. Proficiency in English is typically required, and you may need to submit TOEFL or IELTS scores. Some universities also offer preparatory language courses for students who need to improve their English skills.

2. Are there scholarships available for international students in Cyprus?
Yes, many universities in Cyprus offer scholarships to international students based on academic merit, financial need, or other criteria. These scholarships can help cover tuition fees and living expenses.

3. How much does it cost to live in Cyprus as a student?
The cost of living in Cyprus is relatively low compared to other regions. On average, students might spend between €400 to €800 per month on accommodation, food, transportation, and leisure activities.



